VOICING PLAN:
- Pickup + mm. 1–2: Walking I-V-vi-V quarter-beat harmonic rhythm matches energetic melody; IΔ 7th in m2 for color.
- mm. 3–4: Repeat with inversional variety (m3: V¹, I via different inversions); sus4→resolution in m4 for harmonic interest.
- mm. 5–8: Dark vi7 block in m5 (Eb→Em sub); m6 ii-V with contrary-motion LH; m7 I with chromatic C# in melody only; m8 descending sequence V-I-V-vi.
- mm. 9–12: V7 with C3 in LH at m10 (V7 bass color); m12 V-I-IV-ii cycle.
- mm. 13–16: Climax — IV-vi at m13 (high E); ii-V at m14 (fullest LH); I-IV at m15 (3-note RH at last); full V-I-vi-I-V at m16.
- m17: pedal G1 for resonant final cadence.

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- m6: common tone A4 held RH through ii-V
- m13→m14: E5 common tone bridges IV→vi; then C4 top of LH steps down to resolve
- m15: first time RH has 3 notes (I: G4-B4-D5), marking phrase climax

TEXTURE ARC:
